channel.title: Eminem Songs Compilation
channel.description:
I took 27 Eminem songs and put them into a long paragraph to honor his birthday. I used The Way I Am twice.
"My Mom" took "Purple Pills" because "The Way I Am" made her "Just Loose It", it was "3 AM" and I was on an "8 Mile Road" because I wanted to "Kill You" but "My Mom" was "Cleaning Out My Closet" and found "Kim" and threatened me with "25 to Life". I didn't want to be a "Criminal" so I hit her with a "Medicine Ball" while grabbing "My Balls" and yelling "Here We Go". I rounded up my possy "Like Toy Soldiers" and our group was "Almost Famous" then we hit "Rock Bottom" but had "No Apologies". I was a bad "Role Model" and I was "Saying Goodbye to Hollywood" and "Space Bound" and didn't recognize "The Warning". "The Way I Am" has changed from when I felt like "Superman" and didn't "Sing for the Moment", instead just waited "Till I Collapse" and put the "Nail in the Coffin".
